	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=89024><span id= >Cliana</span></a><br><span id=notbold>72 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I actually had a similar experience myself, though the conditions seemed strange. I just dinged my shaman to 9 and was eagerly giving SoWs to all the youngin's at the Qeynos gate. Summoning my own food and water meant that I was completely self sufficient...<br><br>Well, I decide to whack a few gnoll pups for faction since everyone else seems preoccupied with other mobs, head to the bank, and see a player there, nude. I figure the poor guy is picking up some food for a long corpse run, and drop a SoW and SoB on him. I didn't con him, just buffed, no questions. He checks my equipment... and the next thing I know, he's handing me a Stone Thunder and a Lizardscale Mantle! Considering that I was using a Rusty spear and tattered shoulderpads, I was overjoyed.<br><br>Then the racial problem hit... a Barb couldn't use it. Well crud... I can't just sell such a beautiful gift, so I transfer it over to my cleric... Needless to say... my cleric can now WHOMP!<br><br>While I'm not sure why someone would just give one of these away (other than making the week of a youngin'), I suspect that the reason comes from it's LORE status... and that it doesn't add anything other than a real great ratio. No stat adds or procs... so 'better' weapons can be found, depending on what you want/need. By level 25, a Cleric shouldn't be meleeing anymore... so one would probably want a weapon that increases Wisdom, resists, etc.<br><br>&lt;smirks&gt;I'm not twinked... I just have powerful friends.</p>&nbsp;<br>Cliana Dovien<br>Half-Elf Ranger<br>Tarew Marr<br>Officer of Mistwolf Awakening</td></td></tr>
